<kml>

<concept name=Copy><system-documentation name=Copy>
<superconcept name=Create>

<definition>

  Copy some object, thereby creating a new object with some resemblance
  to the original.

</definition>

<requiredslotlist>

  <slotdescription name=object>
     The thing that's copied, i.e. the "original"
  </slotdescription>

  <slotdescription name=result>
     The thing that's created, i.e. the "copy".
     The resemblance between the object and the result
     is described with extra slots. For example,
     the <slot>shape</slot> of the result = the <slot>shape</slot> of
     the object. 
  </slotdescription>

</requiredslotlist>

<primaryslotlist>

  <slotdescription name=agent>
    the entity that caused the copy.
  </slotdescription>

  <slotdescription name=instrument>
    the tool or aid that was used.
  </slotdescription>

  <slotdescription name=by-means-of>
    the event that caused the copy to occur.
  </slotdescription>

</primaryslotlist>

<examplesentencelist>

  <examplesentence>
    <text>John copied the painting, producing a forgery with identical
color.</text>
    <slotdescription name=agent>John</slotdescription>
    <slotdescription name=object>the painting</slotdescription>
    <slotdescription name=result>a forgery with 
       <slot>color</slot> = the <slot>color</slot> of <slot>object</slot>
    </slotdescription>
  </examplesentence>

  <examplesentence>
    <text>Sam copied the answer from Mary's test. </text>
    <slotdescription name=object>Mary's test</slotdescription>
    <slotdescription name=result>the answer</slotdescription>
    <slotdescription name=agent>Sam</slotdescription>
  </examplesentence>

  <examplesentence>
    <text>Using an advanced lithography process, Julie copied the text. </text>
    <slotdescription name=object>the text</slotdescription>
    <slotdescription name=agent>Julie</slotdescription>
    <slotdescription name=by-means-of>an advanced lithography process</slotdescription>
  </examplesentence>
  <comment>
    The <slot>result</slot> of this copy process is left unstated.  
    Implicitly it is "a copy of the text".
  </comment>

</examplesentencelist>

<neighborlist>

  <neighbor name=Create>
     Create is more general than Copy.  It involves something coming
     into existence, but does not specify a particular process by which 
     this is accomplished.
  </neighbor>

  <neighbor name=Produce>
     Produce involves converting raw materials to order to 
     create the result.
  </neighbor>

</neighborlist>

</kml>


